A Hermosa Beach minister who for years has tried in vain to quell rumors tying

Periodically over the years, Eales said, he would receive threatening phone calls at the church and rectory, and the harassment increased as the McMartin case began to wind down.
Twice in December, the church and rectory were pelted with bottles and rotten eggs.
Then, just days after that assistant pastor resigned, the McMartin verdict came down, and, according to several church members, the anonymous phone calls returned.
His decision shocked and saddened parishioners, who credited Eales with shepherding the church through difficult times.
Said Ron Russell, a 16-year member of the congregation: "We brought a good, strong man in here, and -- well, this has ruined him."
